# iOS take playback audio

All take playback (PiP, review, BestTake, hands-free auto-playback) flows through
ONE output path: the shared Web Audio speaker bus in `takePlaybackSpeaker.ts`
(`source â†’ gain â†’ [enhancer | passthrough] â†’ destination`). The enhancer being
on or off only changes the middle of the chain, never the path.

## The two recurring bugs and their causes

1. **Audio plays ~1s then cuts out** â€” the routed media element was set
   `el.muted = true`. iOS WKWebView throttles/stops decoding muted media
   elements after ~1s, which starves the `MediaElementAudioSourceNode` at the
   SOURCE. No downstream keep-alive can fix this.
2. **Audio is very quiet the whole time** â€” playback fell back to "native-direct"
   (element playing on its own), which routes to the quiet earpiece, or the
   pitch tracker left the shared bus gain at unity (`1`) instead of the boosted
   speaker gain.

## Required pattern (do NOT regress)

1. **Never mute a routed element.** Once `createMediaElementSource(el)` captures
   an element, its output is rerouted into the graph, so leaving it unmuted does
   NOT double-play â€” but it DOES keep iOS decoding. Use
   `applyGraphOutputElementState` (muted=false, volume=1); the `GainNode`
   controls level. This applies in `routeTakePlaybackToSpeaker`,
   `registerTakePlaybackSpeakerRoute`, `TakeVideoPlayer`, the pitch tracker, and
   every `playTakeMedia*` entry point.
2. **One path, always Web Audio.** Do not reintroduce a "native-direct" branch
   for single playback â€” it brought back the quiet-earpiece path. Native element
   output is only a last-resort fallback when `createMediaElementSource` throws.
3. **Boosted gain everywhere.** Output uses `effectiveSpeakerGain(...)`
   (`PLAYBACK_GAIN_NATIVE` â‰ˆ 20Ã— on device). The pitch tracker must NOT reset the
   shared bus gain to `1`; use `applyPitchOutputGain` which defers to the speaker
   module when tapping the shared bus.
4. **Programmatic (non-gesture) audible play**: try unmuted first; if iOS rejects
   it, retry muted then unmute immediately (see `playTakeMediaAudible`).
5. **Capacitor URIs**: never assign raw `file://` to `media.src`; use
   `resolveMediaPlaybackSrc` / `assignMediaPlaybackSrc`.
6. **AVAudioSession** (`AppDelegate.swift`) forces `.speaker` on launch, on
   activate, and on every `routeChangeNotification`. Keep that observer.

Do not re-introduce mic suspension during playback, `AudioSessionPlugin`, or
`playbackKeepAlive` timers â€” they caused regressions.
